History.Adventures in the Gate:
Later on in life, Shandie and her partner Krydle came across two people fleeing from [[the Watch]], the [[elven]] [[sorceress]] [[Delina]] and what appeared to be [[Minsc]], the living embodiment of the [[Beloved Ranger]] statue. The pair of good-hearted thieves agreed to help them flee the city, as Shandie had a soft spot for elves.{{Cite comic/Legends of Baldur's Gate 2|4-8}} They made a deal with [[Osgur Hallorn|the Fetcher]], agreeing to deliver a message to Krydle's father [[Coran]] in exchange for safe passage from Baldur's Gate.{{Cite comic/Legends of Baldur's Gate 2|11-13}}

[[File:Shandie,_taking_aim.png|thumb|left|250px|Sometimes even the best archers...]]
Shandie, Krydle and the two adventurers manage to gain passage into a revel hosted by a Baldurian [[patriar family]], but soon ran afoul of members of the restored [[cult of the Dragon]]. A fight broke out at the grand party, followed by a rooftop chase atop the buildings of the upper city. While Shandie demonstrated her expert skill as an archer, the cultists managed to abduct Delina and return them to their leader, her twin brother [[Deniak]].{{Cite comic/Legends of Baldur's Gate 3|1-20}} 

[[File:Red_dragon,_unimpressed.png|thumb|right|350px|...fail to strike true on their target.]]
Continuing the fight on the side of goodness, the remaining trio tracked down the cultists' hidden lair{{Cite comic/Legends of Baldur's Gate 4|6-8}} and broke in just as Deniak was completing a ritual that used Delina's power to transform himself into a [[red dragon]].{{Cite comic/Legends of Baldur's Gate 4|11-17}} Reunited, the four heroes worked together to down the giant wyrm before it wreaked too much destruction in the city.{{Cite comic/Legends of Baldur's Gate 5|6-17}} After fighting for the good of others, Shandie, Krydle, Minsc, [[Boo]] and Delina decided to continue working together as adventurers.{{Cite comic/Legends of Baldur's Gate 5|19-20}}

History.Domain of Dread:
When taking on a job to protect the [[Temple of Kelemvor (Baldur's Gate)|local temple]] of [[Kelemvor]] in the city,{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 1|5-7}} Shandie and her companions were tested again by a [[werewolf]] attack.{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 1|8-11}} Despite their best efforts, the lycanthropic wolves managed to abduct the [[Kelemvorite]] cleric [[Nerys]] along with numerous [[relic]]s safeguarded at the temple.{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 1|13-15}} Just as they had before, the heroes managed to track down and help free the missing priest. However this time a cloud of [[Domains of Dread|otherworldly]] mist surrounded them and their foes alike, transporting them to the dark realm of [[Barovia]] in the [[Shadowfell]].{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 1|18-24}}{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 2|1}}

[[File:Shandie_Delina_Krydle.png|thumb|right|350px|Shandie, knocking some sense into her companions.]]
The group traveled the strange land for some time, coming across a camp of [[vistani]] caravanners,{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 2|7-8}} and eventually a young vintner whose carriage was assaulted by a pack of vicious [[ghoul]]s. Shandie and her companions saved the young man, [[Adrian Martikov]],{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 2|13-18}} who then proceeded to offer them shelter at the [[Wizard of Wines]] vineyards.{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 3|1-4}} Following Minsc's shift, Shandie took watch as her fellows got some much-needed rest,{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 3|9}} but was forced to prevent her friends from killing one another{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 3|16-18}} when their dreams were haunted by memories of their past.{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 3|11-15}}

After arriving at the fortified town of [[Vallaki]],{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 4|1-2}} the heroes reunited with the werewolves that first brought them to Barovia. They fought off the pack along with their [[vampirism|vampiric]] master [[Sangin]],{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 4|7-17}} but were confronted by none other than Baron [[Strahd von Zarovich]].{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 4|20}} Following Nerys' charge, they attacked Strahd but could not penetrate his defenses. While Shandie was able to nullify some of the vampire lord's illusions,{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 5|2-7}} they were little match for his immense power.{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 5|9-12}} When it appeared they were truly defeated, the curse of Strahd's past manifested and Delina used her arcane power to transport the group back to safety on [[Toril]].{{Cite comic/Shadows of the Vampire 5|13-20}}

History.Return to Faer√ªn:
The adventurers found themselves in the [[Frozenfar|frigid north]] of the Realms, in the [[Spine of the World]] mountains.{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 1|1}} Although the group quickly found shelter from the elements in a cave, Krydle took on a despairing attitude and Shandie had to remind him he was better than that behavior.{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 1|4-7}} After fighting off some [[ogre]]s and meeting a new ally named [[Saarvin]],{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 1|11-17}} they made their way to [[Fireshear]] and got some good rest for the first time in days.{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 2|4-7}} When a band of [[frost giant]]s led by [[Gryttmort]] attacked the isolated settlement, the heroes came to its defense,{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 2|8-17}} and even managed to capture a member of the giant war-band.{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 3|1-4}}

[[File:Shandie_Krydle.png|thumb|left|250px|Facing off against the [[Blades of Burgust]].]]
Shandie and her group learned of Gryttmort's plan to steal an ''[[orb of dragonkind]]'' from the [[white dragon]] [[Nilanthe]] at [[Cold Crag Peak]],{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 3|6-10}} While they were able to briefly ally themselves with Nilanthe by agreeing to recover her eggs from the frost giant's lair,{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 3|12-15}} they could not stop Gryttmort from seizing the orb and taking control of the white dragon's mind.{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 3|16-20}} With the help of Saarvin, [[Dasharra Keldabar]] and local leaders of Fireshear,{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 4|4-5}} The heroes managed to infiltrate the frost giant's glacial lair,{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 4|8-10}}{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 4|12-13}} and draw out the giants into a fierce battle.{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 5|1-7}} Shandie scored a precise shot with her bow on Gryttmort's hand, causing him to drop the ''orb of dragonkind'', freeing the white dragons from his control and turning the tide of the battle in their favor.{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 5|8-10}}{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 5|13}}

True to their word, Shandie and her companions saved Nilanthe's eggs, return to her the ''orb of dragonkind'', and returned to Fireshear as heroes. They celebrated their victory with the townspeople,{{Cite comic/Frost Giant's Fury 5|17-19}} before returning to Baldur's Gate.{{Cite comic/Evil at Baldur's Gate 1|3-4}}

Back in Baldur's Gate, Shandie accompanied Krydle as he uncovered the activities of his old gang, the [[Blades of Burgust]]. Together they helped foil an assassination attempt of Krydle's father [[Coran]], a member of the [[Parliament of Peers]], when the Blades broke into a secret meeting at [[High Hall]].{{Cite comic/Evil at Baldur's Gate 2|8-18}}

After reuniting with their friends at a tavern, Shandie and the others discovered that Nerys had been infected with [[lycanthropy]] during their time in Barovia.{{Cite comic/Evil at Baldur's Gate 4|6-10}} Working with Father Alby of Kelemvor's church, the group helped restrain Nerys in here werewolf form during the [[ritual]] that would purge her of the curse.{{Cite comic/Evil at Baldur's Gate 4|11-13}} They were successful and Nerys was restored to her true self.{{Cite comic/Evil at Baldur's Gate 4|17-20}}
